# .env.example - Copy to .env and customize
# This file provides a template for local configuration.
# The .env file is git-ignored to keep local paths private.

# =============================================================================
# SLICER EXECUTABLE
# =============================================================================
# Path to the Slicer application executable.
# Used by scripts that need to run Slicer (e.g., optimization, testing).

# Linux:
SLICER_PATH=/opt/slicer/Slicer-5.10.0-linux-amd64/Slicer

# macOS:
# SLICER_PATH=/Applications/Slicer.app/Contents/MacOS/Slicer

# Windows:
# SLICER_PATH=C:\Users\user\AppData\Local\NA-MIC\Slicer 5.10.0\Slicer.exe

# =============================================================================
# SLICER SOURCE CODE (Optional)
# =============================================================================
# Path to Slicer source code repository.
# Useful for understanding Slicer internals, module discovery, API details.
# Clone from: https://github.com/Slicer/Slicer.git

# Linux/macOS:
# SLICER_SOURCE=/home/user/projects/slicer/Slicer

# Key directories in Slicer source:
#   Base/Python/slicer/          - Python API (slicer module)
#   Modules/Scripted/            - Built-in scripted modules (examples)
#   Modules/Loadable/Segmentations/ - Segmentation infrastructure
#   Libs/MRML/Core/              - MRML node classes
#   Libs/vtkSegmentationCore/    - Segmentation core classes
